    "policy_language_requires_city_pay_for_misconduct": "Police Union Contract:\nOfficers have paid leave or disability if unfit for duty, including due to substances\nSection 62.2 An employee found to be unfit for duty as a result of a fitness for duty assessment shall be deemed eligible for Paid Leave and Short-Term Disability Benefits\n\nPaid leave for officers involved in police killing, at discretion of Police Chief\nSection 54.1 Employees in classifications listed in Appendix \"A\" may be placed on Administrative Leave With Pay at the discretion of management with the concurrence of the Anaheim City Manager under the following circumstances: 54.1.1 Officers involved in shooting. 54.1.2 Officers suspected of wrongful acts at such times as the best interests of ANAHEIM are served by keeping such officers away from the workplace.",
    "erases_misconduct_records": 0,
