    "erases_misconduct_records": 1,
    "policy_language_erases_misconduct_records": "Policy Manual:\nPrevents internal investigation complaints from being made public.\nSection 1020.8.1 All investigations of personnel complaints, whether originating from a citizen or internally, shall\nbe considered confidential peace officer personnel files. The contents of such files shall not be\nrevealed to other than the involved employee or authorized personnel except pursuant to lawful\nprocess.\n\nPolice Union Contract:\nErases disciplinary actions and reprimands from personnel files within 1-4 years.\nSection 22.2 Police Chief or an authorized designee shall specify the period of time, from one to four years, that the discipline will remain in the affected employee's personnel records, unless a longer period is required by law.",
