    "duty_to_intervene": 1,
    "policy_language_duty_to_intervene": "Yes. \"Duty to Intercede: Any officer present and observing another officer using force that is clearly\n  beyond that which is objectively reasonable under the circumstances shall, when in a position to do\n  so, intercede to prevent the use of such excessive force. Such officers should also report these observations to a supervisor without delay.",
    "requires_warning_before_shooting": 1,
