    "policy_language_gives_officers_unfair_access_to_information": "California Law Enforcement Officer Bill of Rights: Gives officers immediate access to the recorded interrogation\nSection 3303.g The public safety officer being interrogated shall have the right to bring his or her own recording device and record any and all aspects of the interrogation.\n\nPolicy Manual:\nAllows officer to review statement prior to interview\nSection 310.6 The\ninvolved officer shall be provided with a copy of his or her prior statement\nbefore proceeding with any subsequent interview(s). (Govt. Code § 3303(g))\n\nAllows officers to review video recording.\nSection 450.9 When preparing written reports, members should review their recordings as a resource. However,\nmembers should not use the fact that a recording was made as a reason to write a less detailed\nreport.\n\nPermits officers to record interrogations.\nSection 310.6 Administrative interview(s) should be tape recorded by the department (the\nofficer may also record the interview Govt.\nCode § 3303(g))",
