    "policy_language_requires_deescalation": "No. De-escalation only required in limited circumstances.\n300.3 USE OF FORCE\nOfficers shall use only that amount of force that reasonably appears necessary given the facts and circumstances perceived by the officer at the time of the event to accomplish a legitimate law enforcement purpose.\n303.9 KINETIC ENERGY PROJECTILE GUIDELINES\n304.9 TRAINING (CED)\n404.7 CRISIS INEGOTIATION TEAM ADMINISTRATIVE PROCEDURES\n410.4 CONSIDERATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES (5150)\n432.5 FIRST RESPONDERS & 432.6 DE-ESCALATION (mental health crisis)\n434.3 GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS (civil disputes)",
