    "requires_city_pay_for_misconduct": 1,
    "policy_language_requires_city_pay_for_misconduct": "Police Union Contract:\nAllows officers to take paid time off while under investigation\nSection 13.B If a change of assignment, days, or hours of work is not feasible, an officer will be assigned time off with pay.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCity pays when officers discharge firearms off-duty\nSection 44 The City shall indemnify represented employees from any liability claims and costs for personal injury or property damage cuased by the accidental discharge of his/her authorized firearm while off-duty provided that:",
