    "policy_language_requires_deescalation": "300.2.2 WEAPONLESS DEFENSE ARREST TACTICS When practical, verbal commands should be used to gain compliance. If verbal commands have not been effective or are determined to be inappropriate based on the facts and circumstances known to the officer, officers may use that weaponless defense technique and/or arrest tactic which is reasonable to de-escalate the incident and bring it under control as quickly and safely as possible. The following are examples of weaponless defense techniques and arrest tactics that officers may use, but are not limited to: ...",
